{"lemma": "كَبْشٌ", "slug": "كَبْشٌ", "root": "ك.ب.ش", "root_slug": "ك-ب-ش", "root_link": "/words/roots/ك-ب-ش", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 4}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n36607"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B4%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "ram", "fa": "قوچ", "ur": "مینا", "tr": "koç", "id": "domba jantan", "bn": "মেষ", "es": "carnero", "fr": "bélier", "de": "Widder", "ru": "баран", "zh": "公羊"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "ram, male sheep"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "bellwether"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "chieftain, chief, head, leader"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "battering ram"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "A term of cultic significance, borrowed into Arabic from Aramaic, as shown by the consonantism. The late occurrence of Akkadian 𒆏𒋢 (kabsu, “young male sheep”) also implies Aramaic borrowing. Compare Soqotri كبڛ (kobŝ, “ram”).\nRelation with Classical Syriac ܟܒܫܐ (keḇšā, “wether”)\nNöldeke and Fraenkel assumed that Classical Syriac ܟܒܫܐ (keḇšā, “wether”) represented a borrowing from Arabic. This hypothesis was put forth because the /š/ would have been irregular if both the Syriac and Arabic term descended from a shared form with Proto-West Semitic *ś (/⁠ɬ⁠/). This idea was thence repeated in Syriac and Mandaic reference works until the 21st century. However, this cannot be correct, since we would have expected a vocalization *ܟܰܒ݂ܫܳܐ (kaḇšā) - rather than ܟܶܒ݂ܫܳܐ (keḇšā) - if it had been borrowed from Arabic. Additionally, the Syriac term was already borrowed as Old Armenian քաւշ (kʻawš) in the 5th century.\nInstead, the Syriac form is closer to Hebrew כֶּבֶשׂ (kéḇeś, “sheep”) and Phoenician 𐤊𐤁𐤔 (kbš, “sheep”).\nA potential cognate outside of Semitic is Mingrelian ქაბლა (kabla, “calf”). Interestingly, Mingrelian ლ (l) (corresponding to Svan შ (š)) can reflect Proto-Kartvelian *lʿ (/⁠ɬ⁠/), close in pronunciation to Proto-West Semitic *ś (/⁠ɬ⁠/)."}, "ipa": ["/kabʃ/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n36607", "headword_ar": "كَبْشٌ", "root": "kb$", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A ram,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "male sheep, whatever be his age:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a male sheep"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that has entered his third year,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when he has cast his central incisors:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when his tooth that is next to the central pair of incisors has come forth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, K:) [also applied in the present day to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wild sheep of the Arabian and Egyptian deserts and mountains; ovis tragelaphus:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] pl. [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^akobu$N", "text_ar": "اَكْبُشٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^akobaA$N", "text_ar": "اَكْبَاشٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kibaA$N", "text_ar": "كِبَاشٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, K) [and app."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kubuw$N", "text_ar": "كُبُوشٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kubuw$apN", "text_ar": "كُبُوشَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SuquwrapN", "text_ar": "صُقُورَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaqorN", "text_ar": "صَقْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) The female is not called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kabo$apN", "text_ar": "كَبْشَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naEojapN", "text_ar": "نَعْجَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (IJ. [See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAjilapN", "text_ar": "رَاجِلَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] (tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "chief,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lord,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a people, or company of men; (S, K;) their"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "leader:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or their"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "strenuous defender,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "protector,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of them"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to whom others look."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa kabo$u Alkatiybapi", "text_ar": "هُوَ كَبْشُ الكَتِيبَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA) (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He is the leader of the army,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "troop:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "humo kibaA$u", "text_ar": "هُمْ كِبَاشُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlkataAy^ibi", "text_ar": "الكَتَايِبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They are the leaders of the armies,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "troops"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kibaA$N", "text_ar": "كِبَاشٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2589}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Heroes,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "brave men."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) And (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Aged and learned persons."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xrf", "text_ar": "خرف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b3-  [Hence also, (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A buttress:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a corbel which juts out from a wall to support a superstructure:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so in the present day: pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kubuw$N", "text_ar": "كُبُوشٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banawoA suwrFA HaSiynFA wawav~aquwhu biAlkubuw$i", "text_ar": "بَنَوْا سُورًا حَصِينًا وَوَثَّقُوهُ بِالكُبُوشِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They built a strong town-wall, and made it firm with the buttresses"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A, TA.) [See also another ex. voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faSiylN", "text_ar": "فَصِيلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]"}], "source_refs": ["M", "TA", "Lth", "K", "S", "A"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}